        <div class="tips-section">
            <h2 class="filesystem-title">üí° Pro Tips</h2>
            
            <div class="tip-item">
                <h3>üîó Command Chaining</h3>
                <p>Use <code>;</code> to run multiple commands sequentially: <code>ls ; whoami</code></p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-item">
                <h3>üëÅÔ∏è Hidden Files</h3>
                <p>Files starting with <code>.</code> are hidden. Use <code>ls -a</code> to see them all, or <code>ls -A</code> to exclude . and ..</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-item">
                <h3>üõ£Ô∏è Path Types</h3>
                <p><strong>Relative:</strong> <code>cd Desktop</code> | <strong>Absolute:</strong> <code>cd /home/user/Desktop</code></p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-item">
                <h3>üîÑ File Timestamp Tricks</h3>
                <p><code>touch</code> can modify file timestamps without changing content - be aware of security implications!</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip-item">
                <h3>üìÅ Directory Operations</h3>
                <p>Use <code>mkdir -p</code> to create nested directories in one command</p>
            </div>
